The paper deals with probability distributions and their computations, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of factor graphs and hypergraphs suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the analysis of the LBP algorithm and its behaviors falls under statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
